description:
How do you think about faith and works?  Does your life give evidence of fatal flaws in your view of the role of good works? Learn the truth on grace and works.

Is it possible that while we think we grasp the basics of salvation, our lives give evidence of fatal flaws in our understanding? Do we truly understand the relationship between faith and works? What is the role of good works in our salvation? Are we confused about salvation because of our misconceptions on this vital topic?


What is the secret to producing the fruit of the Spirit? How do we become light bearers for God? What is the role of good works in our lives? Why is understanding God’s grace essential to a victorious, joyful Christian experience? And what kind of influence would we have on the world if we really understood God’s grace?


Through stories and practical examples, Pastor Pavel Goia illustrates our confusion over faith and works and reveals a clearer vision of God’s grace.
fulltitle: Pavel Goia - As Righteous as God - Part 3
